{"Body":"<p>In French you can write either “leur femme” or “leurs femmes”; both are considered correct. It is purely an orthographic issue, as the pronunciation is the same in both cases. But to write “leur femme (sing.), qui faisaient (pl.)” seems to me enormously illogical.</p>\n\n<p>In Latin I would definitely say “Venerunt amici cum suis uxoribus”; to say “cum sua uxore” is wrong.</p>\n", "Id":"6074", "ParentId":"6073", "LastEditorUserId":"2556", "CreationDate":"2013-12-05T19:46:55.083", "OwnerUserId":"2556", "PostTypeId":"2", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-12-05T20:18:48.443", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "WebsiteUrl":"", "DownVotes":"3", "Id":"2556", "ProfileImageUrl":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1", "AccountId":"3403950", "Views":"9", "Reputation":"738", "CreationDate":"2013-10-07T16:34:15.923", "DisplayName":"fdb", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-19T01:24:22.827", "AboutMe":""}, "LastActivityDate":"2013-12-05T20:18:48.443", "Score":"0", "CommentCount":"1", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "WebsiteUrl":"", "DownVotes":"3", "Id":"2556", "ProfileImageUrl":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1", "AccountId":"3403950", "Views":"9", "Reputation":"738", "CreationDate":"2013-10-07T16:34:15.923", "DisplayName":"fdb", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-19T01:24:22.827", "AboutMe":""}}